# =============================================================================
# TRIVY IGNORE — Accepted Container Vulnerabilities
# =============================================================================
# Each entry MUST have a comment explaining WHY it's acceptable and WHEN
# it should be revisited. Entries without justification will be removed.
#
# Format: CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
# =============================================================================

# --- Example entries (uncomment and replace when actual CVEs need suppression) ---
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # Low severity in libfoo; no network exposure; revisit Q3 2025
# CVE-2024-YYYYY  # False positive — function not called in our code path
